  "prompt": "Which is the greatest theft that has happened in the history of the world?",
  "response": "Determining the \"greatest\" theft in history can depend on various factors such as the value of what was stolen, the scale of the operation, or the impact it had. However, one of the most famous and substantial thefts in terms of monetary value is the **Great Train Robbery** that took place in the United Kingdom in 1963. A gang managed to stop a Royal Mail train and stole \u00a32.6 million (equivalent to about \u00a353 million today). \n\nAnother significant theft was the **Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum heist** in 1990, where two men stole 13 pieces of artwork valued at over $500 million. This remains the largest private property theft in terms of value and the artwork has never been recovered.\n\nOn a different scale, there was the **heist against the Central Bank of Iraq** in 2003, where nearly $1 billion was taken. This incident is considered the largest bank heist in history.\n\nThese examples each represent significant thefts in terms of either monetary value or cultural value, making any one of them a candidate for the \"greatest\" in its own context.",
